WEBVTT

NOTE
Draft captions derived from the approved narration in demo-script.md /
demo-transcript.md. Cue times follow the script's timing budget (target 6:30).
Before acceptance they must be reconciled against the actual recorded narration;
captions never override what was actually spoken. Synthetic MVP — no customer data.

1
00:00.000 --> 00:04.000
Synthetic MVP — no customer data.

2
00:04.000 --> 00:10.500
An automated offensive-security swarm tests
a customer, then forgets it all afterward.

3
00:10.500 --> 00:17.000
Next quarter it starts from a blank notebook —
no memory of what was open, fixed, or came back.

4
00:17.000 --> 00:25.000
Everything here is a deterministic synthetic MVP:
one Java app, one PostgreSQL database, fixtures.

5
00:25.000 --> 00:35.000
It is not wired into Armadin production.

6
00:35.000 --> 00:43.000
Preflight is read-only — it checks Java, Docker,
the artifact, and the safety guards, changing nothing.

7
00:43.000 --> 00:50.000
Then one command runs the whole demonstration.

8
00:50.000 --> 00:58.000
Engagement 1 is ingested first: every fact is a
tenant-scoped immutable row.

9
00:58.000 --> 01:05.000
It's finalized behind an explicit knowledge boundary.

10
01:05.000 --> 01:12.500
The planner runs at the Engagement 1 boundary,
before any Engagement 2 result exists.

11
01:12.500 --> 01:20.000
It sees opaque candidate IDs only — no labels,
no outcomes, no eventual classification.

12
01:20.000 --> 01:28.000
With memory off, it orders candidates plainly:
T-A, T-B, T-C.

13
01:28.000 --> 01:40.000
With memory on, it uses one persisted fact —
a target previously verified resolved —

14
01:40.000 --> 01:48.000
and rechecks it first: T-C, T-A, T-B.

15
01:48.000 --> 01:58.000
Both plans execute the same frozen outcomes
in separate, identical copies of E1 state.

16
01:58.000 --> 02:10.000
Regression discovery: action three without memory,
action one with memory.

17
02:10.000 --> 02:25.000
Zero Engagement 2 events at planning — nothing leaked.

18
02:25.000 --> 02:34.000
Between engagements the Pod UID, name, and IP
all changed.

19
02:34.000 --> 02:43.000
But the canonical Kubernetes Deployment identity
stayed the same, so the finding is the same finding.

20
02:43.000 --> 02:55.000
A weak collision — a reused DNS name with no
authoritative UID —

21
02:55.000 --> 03:06.000
is held as AMBIGUOUS and changes posture zero times.

22
03:06.000 --> 03:20.000
Weak evidence never silently merges two assets.

23
03:20.000 --> 03:30.000
These are the exact same Engagement 2 facts,
through two knowledge boundaries — no second code path.

24
03:30.000 --> 03:42.000
A stateless scan sees three detections,
one not-detected, one partial,

25
03:42.000 --> 03:52.000
and cannot even represent the finding
that was never retested.

26
03:52.000 --> 04:05.000
Put Engagement 1 memory back in scope
and the same facts gain lifecycle meaning:

27
04:05.000 --> 04:18.000
new, still open, verified resolved, regressed,
not retested, inconclusive.

28
04:18.000 --> 04:30.000
A completed compatible negative verifies
resolution; absence does not.

29
04:30.000 --> 04:44.000
Only the memory view can say a fix came back,
or distinguish verified resolution from a first negative,

30
04:44.000 --> 04:55.000
and flag a known weakness that wasn't retested.

31
04:55.000 --> 05:05.000
Ingestion is deterministic and safe.

32
05:05.000 --> 05:14.000
An identical retry is a no-op;
a conflicting duplicate is rejected.

33
05:14.000 --> 05:24.000
A report is blocked while a completion
sequence is missing.

34
05:24.000 --> 05:34.000
Shuffled arrival order produces the same
report hash.

35
05:34.000 --> 05:45.000
A forced transaction failure leaves no partial state.

36
05:45.000 --> 05:56.000
For Armadin this turns a point-in-time scan
into continuous, longitudinal security:

37
05:56.000 --> 06:06.000
regression detection, verified-resolution tracking,
and coverage honesty.

38
06:06.000 --> 06:18.000
Honest limits: not production-scale, HA, or DR;
not integrated with Armadin.

39
06:18.000 --> 06:30.000
No zero-change-integration, authorization, privacy,
or cross-tenant claims.

40
06:30.000 --> 06:40.000
The internal event contract reduces future
adapter work but does not remove it.

41
06:40.000 --> 06:52.000
The 3-to-1 result, stable identity, the six
classifications, and the correctness checks

42
06:52.000 --> 07:00.000
were computed from executed behavior and
reproduce byte-for-byte. Synthetic MVP, real result.
